      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-1-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "N_\"X\"",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t9-1",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "9-1",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-1-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-1-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-1-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "number of elementary entities of kind stem:[\"X\"] in a system",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The elementary entities must be specified and can be atoms, molecules, ions, electrons, other particle, or a specified group of such particles. It is important to always give a precise specification of the entity involved; this should preferably be done by the empirical chemical formula of the material involved.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-9"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "amount of substance",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-2-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "DEPRECATED: number of moles",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "n(X)",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t9-2",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "9-2",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-2-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-2-1"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-2-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "quotient of number stem:[N] of specified elementary entities of kind stem:[\"X\"] (<<t9-1>>) in a sample, and the Avogadro constant stem:[N_\"A\"] (<<iso80000-1>>):\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nn(\"X\") = (N(\"X\"))/N_\"A\"\n++++\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "Amount of substance is one of the seven base quantities in the International System of Quantities, ISQ (see <<iso80000-1>>).\n\nElementary entities, such as molecules, atoms, ions, electrons, holes and other quasi-particles, double bonds can be used. It is necessary to specify precisely the entity involved, e.g. atoms of hydrogen stem:[\"H\"] vs. molecules of hydrogen stem:[\"H\"_2], preferably by giving the molecular chemical formula of the material involved.\n\nIn the name \"amount of substance\", the words \"of substance\" could be replaced by words specifying the substance concerned, e.g. \"amount of hydrogen chloride, stem:[\"HCl\"]\", or \"amount of benzene, stem:[\"C\"_6\"H\"_6]\".\n\nThe name \"number of moles\" is often used for \"amount of substance\", but this is deprecated because the name of a quantity should be distinguished from the name of the unit.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-mol"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-9"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-3-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "relative atomic mass",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-3-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "A_\"r\"(\"X\")",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t9-3",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "9-3",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-3-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t9-3-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "quotient of the average mass (<<iso80000-4>>) of atom stem:[\"X\"] and the unified atomic mass (<<iso80000-10>>)",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "A similar quantity \"relative molecular mass\" can be defined for molecules.\n\n[example]\n====\nstem:[A_\"r\"(\"Cl\") ~~ 35.453],\n\nstem:[A_\"r\"(\"CO\"_2) ~~ 44].\n====\n\nThe relative atomic or relative molecular mass depends on the nuclidic composition.\n\nThe International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC) accepts the use of the special names \"atomic weight\" and \"molecular weight\" for the quantities \"relative atomic mass\" and \"relative molecular mass\", respectively. The use of these traditional names is deprecated.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-9"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t9-4-0",
