      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "for substance stem:[\"X\"] in a mixture, quotient of amount stem:[n_\"X\"] of substance (<<t9-2>>) of stem:[\"X\"] and volume stem:[V] (<<iso80000-3>>) of the mixture\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nc_\"X\" = n_\"X\"//V\n++++\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "In chemistry, the name \"amount-of-substance concentration\" is generally abbreviated to the single word \"concentration\", it being assumed that the adjective \"amount-of-substance\" is intended. For this reason, however, the word \"mass\" should never be omitted from the name \"mass concentration\" in <<t9-10>>.\n\nDecided by the 16^th^ CGPM (1979), both \"l\" and \"L\" are allowed for the symbols for the litre.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
